### Handshake

```json
{
  "protocolVersion": "2025-11-25",
  "capabilities": { "tools": {} },
  "serverInfo": { "name": "ddr-mcp", "version": "<version>" }
}
```

### Input schema

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["query"],
  "properties": {
    "query": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Natural language question. E.g. 'why is the cache invalidated on write instead of using a TTL?'"
    },
    "limit": {
      "type": "integer",
      "default": 3,
      "minimum": 1,
      "maximum": 10,
      "description": "Maximum results to return. Keep low — the agent should read these carefully."
    }
  }
}
```

### Chunking strategy

If the text has markdown headings (H2/H3), split on heading boundaries. Otherwise, treat the entire text as one section. Then apply token-window sliding within any section that exceeds `chunk_size`.

```
body = full file content

if body has H2/H3 headings:
  split on heading boundaries
else:
  treat body as single section

for each section:
  if section_tokens <= chunk_size:
    emit as one chunk
  else:
    slide window (chunk_size, chunk_overlap) within the section
```

Each chunk carries the source document's path and title so any chunk hit can produce a complete result without re-reading the source file.

---

## Error Handling

All MCP errors use standard JSON-RPC 2.0 error objects with a structured `data` field.

```json
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "error": {
    "code": -32602,
    "message": "Invalid params",
    "data": {
      "field": "limit",
      "reason": "must be between 1 and 10"
    }
  }
}
```

Startup failures (missing index, version mismatch, bad config) are printed to stderr and exit with code 1 before the MCP handshake.

